# Component identity (permanent)

Apply these rules whenever creating, updating, importing, or migrating smart components / ingredients.

## Company code

- Every company has an immutable 4-letter `Code` (A–Z), auto-created from the company name when missing.
- Short names are padded with `X`. Colliding names get a unique suffix letter/digit.
- Locations inherit the company catalog; uniqueness is never scoped per location.

## Component name

- Unique within a company (case-insensitive).
- Normalize by trimming, collapsing repeated spaces to one space, and rejecting characters other than letters, digits, spaces, and `-`.
- `"Flour  "` / `" flour"` / `"Flour"` are the same name and must not create a second Component ID.
- On collisions in legacy data: merge duplicates into the oldest row and remount all related string references to the keeper.

## Component ID

- Format: `{COMPANY_CODE}-{XXXX}` where `XXXX` is 4 uppercase alphanumeric characters containing **at least one letter and one number** (e.g. `BISY-A001`).
- Assigned by the API only. Clients may preview, never invent final authority.
- After creation, treat Component ID as immutable in the public API.
- When changing IDs, update denormalized copies (`PurchaseOrderItems`, inventory, movements, recipes that match ingredient IDs, wastage/transfer `ItemKey` for `component`, archives via remap table). Do not rewrite product numeric IDs stored in recipe `ComponentId` fields.

